Computes the set of elements contained in either of the two specified sets but not in both. That is, set diff1 = set1 - set2 and diff2 = set2 - set1.

Type Parameters:
T - - static generic type reference
Parameters:

set2 - - Second set.
diff1 - pre-condition: non null; post-condition: contains the asymmetric set difference set1 - set2.
diff2 - pre-condition: non null; post-condition: contains the asymmetric set difference set2 - set1.
set - pre-condition: non-null; post-condition:unspecified. This Set allows a comparator to be specified.
